"title": "5504: rights",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5504: rights",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The basis of a claim to respect, and just and fair treatment. God has rights over his creation as a result of his sovereignty and authority. Through being the height of his creation, human beings also have rights, which are to be respected.</p>\n<h2>The rights that God gives</h2>\n<h3>God gives rights to the poor and needy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:22\">EXO 22:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:25-Exod22:27\">EXO 22:25–22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:9-Lev19:10\">LEV 19:9–19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job36:6\">JOB 36:6</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to slaves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:11\">LEV 22:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2-Exod21:6\">EXO 21:2–21:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:12-Deut15:18\">DEU 15:12–15:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:7-Exod21:11\">EXO 21:7–21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:26-Exod21:27\">EXO 21:26–21:27</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to strangers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:33-Lev19:34\">LEV 19:33–19:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21\">EXO 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:10\">LEV 19:10</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to those who commit manslaughter</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:9-Num35:12\">NUM 35:9–35:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:41-Deut4:42\">DEU 4:41–4:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh20:1-Josh20:6\">JOS 20:1–20:6</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights in marriage</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:3-1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:3–7:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:7-Exod21:11\">EXO 21:7–21:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:21\">DEU 22:13–22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:33\">EPH 5:22–5:33</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to parents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1\">EPH 6:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:4\">1TI 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16\">HEB 12:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:29-Gen25:34\">GEN 25:29–25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:15-Deut21:17\">DEU 21:15–21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:1-1Chr5:2\">1CH 5:1–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:4\">EPH 6:4</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to Christians</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26-Gal4:7\">GAL 3:26–4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:14\">REV 22:14</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:18\">1CO 9:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:1-1Cor9:17\">1CO 9:1–9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17-1Tim5:18\">1TI 5:17–5:18</a></p>\n<h2>Why God gives rights</h2>\n<h3>God gives rights to keep an orderly society</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:29\">LEV 19:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:1-Deut15:6\">DEU 15:1–15:6</a></p>\n<h3>God gives rights to protect people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:15\">DEU 19:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:23-Lev25:43\">LEV 25:23–25:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:47-Lev25:55\">LEV 25:47–25:55</a></p>\n<h2>The defence of rights</h2>\n<h3>God, the defender of rights</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:8-Mic7:10\">MIC 7:8–7:10</a></strong> <em>The implied speaker here is Israel.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:18\">DEU 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:5\">PSA 68:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:10-Prov23:11\">PRO 23:10–23:11</a></p>\n<h3>Abuse of rights punished by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:1-Isa10:4\">ISA 10:1–10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:26-Jer5:29\">JER 5:26–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6-Amos2:8\">AMO 2:6–2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Leaders are to protect the rights of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:1-Ps72:4\">PSA 72:1–72:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:4-Prov31:9\">PRO 31:4–31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:8\">ECC 5:8</a></p>\n<h2>The rights which God has</h2>\n<h3>God has a right to be worshipped</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:36\">2KI 17:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10\">MAT 4:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13\">DEU 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:24\">JHN 4:24</a></p>\n<h3>God has a right to be obeyed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12-Deut10:13\">DEU 10:12–10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:16-Deut26:18\">DEU 26:16–26:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:16\">DEU 30:16</a></p>",
